Interface Identifiable<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the class type of the identifier.
    All Superinterfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    Function
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BootstrappingFunction, CreateRegionFunction, FunctionAdapter, RegionSizeFunction, TouchPartitionedRegionEntriesFunction, TouchReplicatedRegionEntriesFunction

    public interface Identifiable<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
extends java.io.Serializable
    The Identifiable interface defines a contract for classes whose Object instances can be uniquely identified relative to other Object instances within the same class type hierarchy.

    Since:
    7.0
    See Also:
    Comparable
